'''Berk''' is a [[slang]] term derived from [[cockney rhyming slang]]. It is a shortened version of [[Berkeley Hunt]], the [[hunting with hounds|hunt]] based at [[Berkeley Castle]] in [[Gloucestershire]], or possibly the [[Berkshire Hunt]]. In the rhyming slang, "hunt" is made to rhyme with [[cunt]] giving the word berk its original slang meaning.<ref>[[Oxford English Dictionary]]: Entry for berk</ref>  It is not perceived to be excessively rude, perhaps because whilst it is known for being a slang word, its real meaning is not well known. Similar to Charlie Hunt as in "he's a right Charlie" another cockney saying - Charlie Hunt being a local eastend figure of the time this saying was common

It is also, perhaps more commonly, used to mean [[idiot]], in an affectionate sense.

